title: Check Anagram
description: Write a Python function that checks whether two strings are anagrams of each other.
constraints: Constraints: The strings will contain only alphabetic characters.
test:
def passTest():
	solution = Solution()
	param = [[silent, listen], [hello, world], ['the eyes', 'they see'], ['abc', 'abcd'], ['Listen', 'Silent']]
	ans = [True, False, True, False, True]
	for i in range(5):
		if ans[i] == solution.isAnagram(param[i][0], param[i][1]):
			continue
		else
			return False
	return True
passedTest = 'Passed all test cases' if passTest() else 'Test cases failed'
print(passedTest)
